<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000053#     1#          153#">Va. Code Ann. § 53.1-153</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_53.1-153"/><heading><desig>§ 53.1-153.</desig><title>Eligibility of persons sentenced to jails for more than twelve months</title></heading><bodyText><p>Persons convicted of felonies or misdemeanors who are sentenced to jails and not eligible for parole under <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 53.1-152"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 53.1-152">§ 53.1-152<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000053#     1#          152#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, shall be eligible for parole in the same manner as provided in <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 53.1-151"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 53.1-151">§ 53.1-151<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000053#     1#          151#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> when the total sentences to be served, exclusive of fines, are more than twelve months. However, a person convicted of misdemeanors and sentenced to serve a total active sentence of more than 12 months in jail shall not be eligible for parole nor subject to the provisions of <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 53.1-159"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 53.1-159">§ 53.1-159<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000053#     1#          159#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> upon conviction of any offenses committed on or after July 1, 2008.</p><p>The Virginia Parole Board shall have the same powers and duties to carry out the provisions of this section as are set forth in <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 53.1-136"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 53.1-136">§ 53.1-136<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000053#     1#          136#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p>Code 1950, § 53-251.2; 1962, c. 326; 1970, c. 648; 1981, c. 392; 1982, c. 636; 1983, c. 509; <citation normalizedCite="2008 VA CH 846"><content><span normalizedCite="2008 Va. Ch. 846">2008, c. 846<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2008#000846#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></historyItem></historyGroup></history></level></statute></legislativeDocBody><metadata><dc:metadata xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><dc:identifier identifierScheme="PGUID">urn:contentItem:5K0Y-PT80-004G-K1SP-00000-00</dc:identifier><dc:source sourceScheme="productContentSetIdentifier">10816</dc:source><dc:date dateType="last-updated">2016-06-15</dc:date></dc:metadata><publicationInfo><publicationName>CODE OF VIRGINIA </publicationName><copyright>Copyright © 2016  by Matthew Bender &amp; Company, Inc. a member of the LexisNexis Group. All rights reserved</copyright></publicationInfo><hierarchy><hierarchyLevel levelType="title"><heading><desig>TITLE 53.1.</desig><title>PRISONS AND OTHER METHODS OF CORRECTION</title></heading><hierarchyLevel levelType="chapter"><heading><desig>CHAPTER 4.</desig><title>PROBATION AND PAROLE</title></heading><hierarchyLevel levelType="article"><heading><desig>ARTICLE 3.</desig><title>PR